title: Sources: KD out at least 2 weeks with calf strain
description: Suns star Kevin Durant is out at least two weeks due to a left calf strain, sources told ESPN.
author: Shams Charania

title: Georgia Tech stings Miami, hands Canes 1st loss
description: Haynes King led Georgia Tech to a 28-23 win over previously unbeaten No. 4 Miami on Saturday, the Yellow Jackets' first win over a top-five team in 15 years.

title: Salt century fires England to victory in first T20
description: Phil Salt powers a superb century to take England to a commanding eight-wicket victory over West Indies in the first T20 in Barbados.

title: Stunning Salt century fires England to opening win over West Indies
description: Phil Salt smashed an unbeaten 103 off 54 balls as England chased down 183 in just 16.5 overs to beat West Indies by eight wickets in the first T20 international in Barbados.

title: Shock Grand Slam loss for Humphries as Littler wins in six minutes
description: Reigning champion Luke Humphries suffered a shock defeat to Rowby-John Rodriguez in Group A as Luke Littler sent out a message from Group F with a 5-0 drubbing of Keane Barry to get off to a perfect start on his Grand Slam of Darts debut.
